00:02:14.260 --> 00:02:20.400
And so today's
roadmap is titled--

00:02:20.400 --> 00:02:22.240
headlined-- "Sounds
Localization."

00:02:22.240 --> 00:02:25.620
And we're going to be talking
about the kind of localization

00:02:25.620 --> 00:02:29.275
using binaural cues,
where you have two ears.

00:02:30.610 --> 00:02:35.100
And because you have two ears
and because sound sources

00:02:35.100 --> 00:02:39.250
are located off your
midline for the most part,

00:02:39.250 --> 00:02:45.120
we have some very prominent
cues called Interaural Time

00:02:45.120 --> 00:02:50.330
Differences, ITDs, and
Interaural Level Differences,

00:02:50.330 --> 00:02:50.830
ILDs.

00:02:54.950 --> 00:02:58.450
OK, so we'll talk about what
